            <biogHist>
                <p>Malcolm MacPhail was born to Angus MacPhail, crofter, and Catherine MacPhail n√©e
                    McLeod in Shawbost. MacPhail studied at the University and New College,
                    Edinburgh. In 1877 he was ordained at Kilmartin and the following year he
                    married Isabella Catherine MacKenzie, and they had at least one son.</p>
                <p>Malcolm died of paralytic shock in December 1906 and his son H.W. MacPhail signed
                    the register. </p>
                <p>CW108 contains folklore that was probably collected by Rev Malcolm MacPhail and
                    transcribed from his papers by Alexander Carmichael.</p>
